spans.text: like His Grace , Perhaps related to the race
them wha Maun please the Great-folk for a wamefou
the Rake that takes the door
with his sweeping besom , Just frets till Heaven commission gies him
the ever-deep'ning tones , Still louder shrieks
it proper , When of my works I did review , To dedicate them , Sir , to YOU

For prayin I hae little skill oed ; I'm baith dead-sweer , and wretched ill oed ; But I'se repeat each poor man's prayer , That kens or hears about you , Sir — ' May never Misfortune's gowling bark , ' Howl through the dwelling oF the CLERK
For who would humbly serve the Poor
